      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 83: The minimum-size clamp can break the video\u0027s aspect ratio when `minimumHeight` is larger than `newWidth * r`. The comment says the resulting proportions exactly match `r`, but the current code only clamps width before deriving height, then independently clamps height without recalculating width. This can leave the PiP letterboxed/cropped contrary to the change intent. Recompute the paired dimension after any minimum-height clamp.\n```suggestion\nnewWidth \u003d Math.max(minimumWidth, Math.round(Math.sqrt(area / r)));\nnewHeight \u003d Math.round(newWidth * r);\nif (newHeight \u003c minimumHeight) {\n    newHeight \u003d minimumHeight;\n    newWidth \u003d Math.max(minimumWidth, Math.round(newHeight / r));\n}\n```",
